Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.76,0:00:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, at this time I'd like to introduce\NDr. Hawkins.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.88,0:00:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Where do I go?\NWhere do I go? Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.80,0:00:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Do I go there?\N>> Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.84,0:00:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You were calling me a relic.\NI'm not old enough to be a relic.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.48,0:00:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm a pre prelic.\NSo glad to see you all today.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.68,0:00:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And uh the weather is just perfect\Nand people came from long distances
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.16,0:01:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and so we try to stay as strictly\Nadhered to time and time limitations.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.07,0:01:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And uh the lecture for today is on\Nfreedom, morality and ethics. Freedom.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.88,0:01:13.43,Default,,0,0,0,,morality and ethics\Nin uh in today's world especially in the
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.43,0:01:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,week just finished.\NThere's vague boundaries between uh
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.11,0:01:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,freedom and morality and ethics. Uh how\Nmuch freedom can you have before you
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.88,0:01:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,cross over into immorality\Nand a lack of ethics? Uhhuh. And so
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.64,0:01:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,discernment discernment is the answer.\NAnd so that will really be the focus of
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.40,0:01:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,today, discernment.\NHow to differentiate between freedom and
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.32,0:01:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,uh\Nand what does this word here say? What
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.92,0:01:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,does that say?\NWhat does that say?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.36,0:01:56.39,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Writing.\N>> Insurrection.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.39,0:01:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,>> No.\N>> Treason.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.28,0:02:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Revolt.\N>> Oh well.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.24,0:02:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,anarchy.\NThere we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.80,0:02:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Thanks.\N>> To differentiate when is freedom freedom
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.52,0:02:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and when is it just anarchy?\NWhen is it constructive and when is it
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.04,0:02:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,destructive?\NWhen does it take you to liberation or
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.04,0:02:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,when does it take you to enslavement?\NAnd so we'll discuss that. It's a very
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.56,0:02:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,uh interesting subject and of course\Nit's been discussed over the centuries
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.92,0:02:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,from the days of ancient Greece until\Ncurrent time
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.40,0:02:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,in the days of ancient Greece and the\Nphilosophy of ancient Greece etc were
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.59,0:02:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,the kind of things that preoccupied my\Nmind as an adolescent.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.12,0:02:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,There were three of us that hung\Ntogether and uh we spent our our boyhood
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.80,0:03:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,listening to classical music. arguing\Nphilosophy, Plato and Socrates
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.48,0:03:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and uh while the other kids were playing\Nstickball so I don't know which one of
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.15,0:03:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,us was\Nrecently one member of the team so that
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.20,0:03:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,was what 75 70 years ago\None one of them went west there were
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.12,0:03:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,three of us one of them went west and\Nbecame a geologist
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.48,0:03:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and the third one is now a professor and\NI hadn't heard from him in 60 years I
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.20,0:03:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,think and suddenly they got a a message\Nfrom him that he had discovered me. And
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.48,0:03:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,uh so I've got gotten together in\Ncommunication with a friend from from
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.00,0:03:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,seven 70 years ago\N70 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.28,0:03:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,what welded us together was classical\Nmusic and the aesthetics not only uh
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.44,0:03:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,intellectual\Nbut the aesthetics of the intellectual
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.20,0:04:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,which is even a greater refinement\Nand so I thought that's very interesting
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.04,0:04:05.51,Default,,0,0,0,,how time like stops and then suddenly\Nstarts again like 70 years had never
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.51,0:04:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,even gone by very interesting\Nso today we we're going to do our slides
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.68,0:04:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and then at 10:15 we have a break is\Nthat correct Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.36,0:04:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,>> 10:15. So I better start\N>> 11:15.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.68,0:04:25.91,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Oh, 11:15.\NUh, all right. You'll let me know. Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.91,0:04:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Time is somewhere. I don't know what I'm\Nthe time on the way here. Now, let's
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.91,0:04:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,see. Let's look at the slides for today.\NUh, we always start with a review. Uh, a
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.40,0:04:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,short review depending on how many new\Npeople we have here today. Uh, the new
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.88,0:04:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,people raise your hands. So we can see\Nhow many are here. Oh, it's a sizable
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.44,0:04:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,number. Oh, wave your hands. Oh,\Nthere there's all the new people. All
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.28,0:05:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,right. So for the sake of those who\Nhaven't been here before and as a review
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.80,0:05:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,for people that have been uh we do an\Nabbreviated review of some of the major
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.19,0:05:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,uh topics in the development of this\Nwhole field of consciousness research.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.63,0:05:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that does it stay way up there? Is\Nthat where it stays
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.32,0:05:30.80,Default,,0,0,0,,>> now? You didn't tell me that before.\NWell, let's see now. What do we do about
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.80,0:05:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that?\N>> You jump high.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.32,0:05:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, let's see then. Then I need to see\Nwhat slides we're reviewing. There we
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.08,0:05:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,are. Okay, now watch out.\NAll right. So I I remember where we are
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.24,0:06:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,now.\NI remember where we are. We're right
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.32,0:06:05.91,Default,,0,0,0,,here and it's right now. That solves it.\NSo we got to start with the map of
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.91,0:06:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness which evolved over a\Nnumber of decades and uh really refle
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.08,0:06:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,reflects the perennial wisdom. This is\Nreally the perennial wisdom and it's
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.52,0:06:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,pretty much in alignment with\Npsychoanalytic theory and uh great
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.96,0:06:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,numerous philosophies\Nuh in in which the the states into which
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.03,0:06:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,man to which a man may become aligned or\Neventually imprisoned
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.19,0:06:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,uh are are put in a and we are put in a\Na line of decreasing integrity.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.63,0:06:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So we start with the most integrous and\Nthen we move on to man's lower nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.12,0:06:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So here we have above the line man's\Nhigher nature you might say and below
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.80,0:07:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the line man's lower nature.\Nuh the lower nature is often
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.36,0:07:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,emerges with the animal instincts of\Nkill and be killed and and hate and
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.40,0:07:16.31,Default,,0,0,0,,the extremes of emotion from high to\Nlow. So during this recent election, we
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.31,0:07:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,saw uh this displayed very well across\Nthe television land uh from the most
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.19,0:07:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,despicable kinds of comments uh to the\Nmost uplifting. And we ended up happily
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.03,0:07:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,on a very uplifting note. And now we're\Nall waiting with baited breath to see
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.36,0:07:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,what kind of a dog goes in the White\NHouse.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.91,0:07:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I think that's very endearing. You know,\Nwhen all the war is put away, everybody
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.31,0:07:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,gets down to reality. And what's really\Nimportant is what kind of a doggy is it
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.12,0:07:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,going to be there? You know, I remember\NFranklin D. Roosevelt, you always had f
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.56,0:08:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,follow with him. Follow him with a\Nlittle black Scotty and FDR have the dog
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.80,0:08:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,talking to the great powers of the world\Nwith Fala. He wouldn't try without Fala.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.63,0:08:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So those things are the the contrast\Nbetween uh the most severe, evil, and
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.24,0:08:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,hopeless with the most endearing and\Nencouraging. So long as we worry about
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.68,0:08:25.12,Default,,0,0,0,,what kind of a dog is in the warehouse,\Nour country is safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.12,0:08:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Because why? Because it shows that the\Nheart the heart in the end is the heart
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.91,0:08:35.83,Default,,0,0,0,,that wins. It's the heart that wins, is\Nit not? Because even even the candidate
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.83,0:08:42.08,Default,,0,0,0,,that won really to a great degree won\Nbecause of the heart uh involved. There
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.08,0:08:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,was the strict politicians and some\Nbecame quite vicious. But in the end it
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.60,0:08:52.39,Default,,0,0,0,,you know it was the heart that people\Ncheered. So when people cheered they
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.39,0:08:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,said well it's a a new breakthrough for\NAmerica. and but they meant from the
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.16,0:09:02.95,Default,,0,0,0,,heart from the heart\Nthat we're all truly equal not just in
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.95,0:09:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,words but in deeds.\NSo that was very uh supportive and uh
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.88,0:09:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and I think it signals perhaps a very\Ngood era upcoming era despite the
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.44,0:09:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,economic situations.\NAll right. So here we have the the
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.24,0:09:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,classical levels of consciousness and\Nthe emotions that go with them. And of
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.56,0:09:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,course we then calibrated them and this\Nis the process going on in
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.36,0:09:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness. Uh so the beginning of\Nthis work was really the discovery of uh
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.80,0:09:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,how to calibrate things. And the way it\Ncame about is we discovered that certain
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.44,0:09:51.27,Default,,0,0,0,,things made people go weak and other\Nthings made people go strong. Anything
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.27,0:09:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,that's pro-life makes you go strong and\Nanything that's anti-life makes you go
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.68,0:09:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,weak.\NThat was demonstrated in an early
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.44,0:10:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,lecture in kinesiology.\NAnd uh it was the energy that caused
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.76,0:10:11.20,Default,,0,0,0,,this diff differential between strong\Nand weak. Then the next thing I was
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.20,0:10:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,lecturing on this subject to the staff\Nat the clinic. I would go around to all
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.07,0:10:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,these\Nlectures and and and pull bring back to
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.48,0:10:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the clinic what whatever I thought was\Nuseful to the staff and the most
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.04,0:10:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,interesting thing one of the most\Ninteresting things although people poo
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.04,0:10:33.51,Default,,0,0,0,,poo kinesiology I'll tell you one thing\Nthey can't poo poo and that is when
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.51,0:10:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,people look at a fluorescent light\Nuh about half the audience will go weak
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.32,0:10:44.39,Default,,0,0,0,,certain people will look at a\Nfluorescent light and go weak other
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.39,0:10:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,people look at the fluorescent light and\Ndo not go weak and we discovered that
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.36,0:10:53.83,Default,,0,0,0,,the people who did not go weak. So when\NI was going to demonstrate it to the to
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.83,0:11:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,the clinic staff I needed some\Nvolunteers. So we had at the same time
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.12,0:11:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,the course of miracles people we had an\Nattitudinal healing center the second
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.44,0:11:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,one in the United States\Nfor uh people with hopeless chronic uh
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.24,0:11:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,incurable conditions.\NAnd uh so when I needed volunteers, I
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.60,0:11:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,they were standing around. So I said,\N"Come on over here. I want to
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.39,0:11:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,demonstrate something."\NAnd uh so when they looked at the
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.60,0:11:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,fluorescent light, they did not go weak.\NHuh. So when we picked some other
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.83,0:11:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,strangers from the audience, you might\Nsay, they did go weak. So what was it
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.92,0:11:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,about the people doing a course of\Nmiracles? Why didn't they go weak when
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.92,0:11:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,looking at a fluorescent light?\NSo fluorescent lights don't have to do
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.07,0:11:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,with good and evil. They don't have to\Ndo with religion or belief systems, but
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.48,0:11:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,some physiologic capacity to\Ndifferentiate that which is pro-life,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.07,0:11:58.95,Default,,0,0,0,,that which is anti-life.\NSo we made I made a clinical study out
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.95,0:12:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,of this group and uh\Nwe started with a new group of about
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.12,0:12:09.60,Default,,0,0,0,,four or five people who were just\Nstarting the course of miracles. So I
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.60,0:12:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,took them out of the group that went\Nweek four or five people and um they
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.20,0:12:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,began to do the course of miracles and\Nthen we retested them every week or
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.12,0:12:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,every month I forget what it was and by\Nthe time they got to about lesson I
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.80,0:12:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,forget 80 or 90\N>> 75
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.60,0:12:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,>> 75 all right so these people who went\Nweak when they looked at the fluorescent
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.51,0:12:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,lights by about less than 75 in a course\Nof miracles no longer went weak isn't
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.00,0:12:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that incredible\NIncredible.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.32,0:12:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you can poo poo it all you want.\NIt's a fact. And the people who poo poo
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.88,0:12:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,what I'm lecturing about all go week.\NThat's a fact. Some famous professors.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.76,0:12:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,They're very famous professors. Get out\Nthere and poo poo Hawkins and all what
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.20,0:13:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,he says on. And then when I did the arm\Non them, I went weak. They were all
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.27,0:13:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,atheists. Yeah. Every one of them. Uh so\Nwe found out that this uh means of
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.88,0:13:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,discerning truth from falsehood does not\Nwork for atheists. So if you're an
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.92,0:13:23.83,Default,,0,0,0,,atheist, don't waste your time doing it.\NThose that deny the source of truth are
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.83,0:13:28.39,Default,,0,0,0,,denied the fruits thereof is what it\Namounted to
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.39,0:13:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,that. And and these professors was not\Npublicly known they were atheists, but
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.92,0:13:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,we discovered that it was so. All right.\NSo this was a very mind-boggling. You
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.12,0:13:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,know, I'm a clinician and to me what\Nimpresses me is what works. When you got
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.00,0:13:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,a sick patient, I don't care about\Ntheories and what's approved and what's
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.36,0:13:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,not approved. You tell people what\Nworks. What works.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.16,0:13:55.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Right now, for instance, I had to go for\Nacupuncture. I I I tore the what do you
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.27,0:14:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,call it? Rotator cuff of the left\Nshoulder. The my dog pulled me down and
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.80,0:14:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,it was the dog's fault. bad dog\Nmade me fall on the cement
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.68,0:14:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and I tore this rotator cuff. So, I've\Nbeen seeing an acupuncturist. Yeah. And
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.68,0:14:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,immediately I got I got immediate help\Nfrom it. And of course, they always lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.56,0:14:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,They say the needles aren't going to\Nhurt, but they lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.07,0:14:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,They lie. So,\Nso I have a patch, a warmer patch with
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.16,0:14:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,oriental herbs in it. And I see an\Nacupuncturist. So, you can see I'm not
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.56,0:14:42.95,Default,,0,0,0,,exactly going to meet the approval of\Nthe American Medical Association.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.95,0:14:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. So, acupuncture, I've told\Nthat story before, is what cured my
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.56,0:14:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,chronic intractable ulcer. And I saw the\Nfirst I was one of the first acupuncture
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.51,0:14:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,patients in the United States. The first\Nclinic was in Washington DC. It was only
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.80,0:15:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,by the approval of the federal\Ngovernment in the federal health
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.88,0:15:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,services and uh so I used to fly from\NNew York once a week down to uh
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.12,0:15:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Washington from New York and uh they you\Nhad to bring all your X-rays and proof
